jobs.description:
Jessica Lucich is a Manager in PwC Australia’s Corporate Advisory legal practice based in Sydney. 

The Corporate Advisory team's areas of expertise include:
- managed investment schemes;
- financial services and credit licensing;
- mergers and acquisitions, private entity and inbound investments;
- corporate restructures, with experience across both domestic and international reorganisations;
- initial public offerings and other capital markets transactions;
- entity governance and compliance;
- private equity and venture capital;
- joint venture arrangements;
- foreign investment rules;
- technology and intellectual property matters; and
- general corporate and commercial advice and documentation.

Rotations for Clerkship included:
- Intellectual Property where I completed a variety of litigious, regulatory advice and research work for pharmaceutical companies, telecommunication providers, brand name retailers and luxury good designers. I was exposed broadly to all areas of IP including patents, trademarks, copyright and passing off issues;
- Major Projects (Energy, Resources, Infrastructure and Corporate) where I took part in both public and private M&A transactions. A considerable amount of work comprised of completing due diligence for large scale and complex transactions, as well as drafting and organising a variety of documents for completion and post-completion;
- One week secondment to CISCO; and
- Repeated exposure to cross-border work and international clients.

general.description:
Associate at Baker McKenzie in the Dispute Resolution practice group.

I completed rotations in the Construction, Employment and Dispute Resolution practice groups.

Through my rotations I have developed a particular interest in commercial litigation and dispute resolution having assisted with a variety of disputes in the following fields:
-construction law;
-competition and consumer law;
-employment and industrial law;
environmental and regulatory law; and
-commercial contracting.

Monash Law/Arts graduate with a double major in French and Spanish.

I am an experienced employment practitioner with almost 10 years of experience advising clients in respect of employment and workplace relations law in both Australia and the UK.

My practice includes:

- advising on employment matters including pre-employment issues, minimum legislative requirements, the operation of industrial instruments, protection of business interests via post employment restraints;

- advising on independent contractor and employment relationship, including drafting independent contractor agreements and employment contracts;

- drafting, and advising on, employment policies and procedures;

- advising on employment termination matters including performance management, misconduct, negotiated termination arrangements and release agreements;

- advising on options and risks associated with the termination of employment of senior executives and the associated Corporations Act considerations;

- providing representation and advice to employers in relation to unfair dismissal and general protections claims, including representing employers at conciliation conferences before the Fair Work Commission;

- providing advice and representation to employers in relation to common law breach of contract claims and Australian Consumer Law claims, including representation at mediations before the Federal Circuit Court of Australia; and

- providing advice and representation to employers in discrimination complaints and applications for review of administrative decisions in the Administrative Decisions Tribunal / New South Wales Civil and Administrative Tribunal and HROEC.

I have experience working with clients across a broad range of industries, both in the public and private sectors, including banking and finance, telecommunications, transport, manufacturing, retail and pharmaceutical.

